Overview.Summary: The 2020 British Grand Prix, located in the United Kingdom, has been affected by COVID-19 and had its schedule delayed (9). Several TV broadcasters, including Channel 4, have announced they will air the GP (2). The British GP is in the Mercedes team schedule (5). Great Britain does have the fourth most wins of any nation in Formula 1 (8).

Timeline.Text: The British Grand Prix and MotoGP races are scheduled to take place in the 2020 season.
British driver Lewis Hamilton competes in the Italian Formula One Grand Prix at the Autodromo Nazionale circuit in Monza.
The 2021 Formula One season's race schedule is announced, with the British Grand Prix set to take place on July 18th.
British auto racing magazine, Autosport International, features a panel on the history of the British Grand Prix.
British Grand Prix promoter Ian Forest issues a statement about the future of the race at Donington Park.
Scottish rock band, Mogwai, performs at the British Grand Prix.
The 2020 British Grand Prix is broadcast live on free TV channels in the UK.

Overview.Summary: At the 2020 British Grand Prix, Charles Leclerc placed third behind Hamilton and Verstappen (2). In 2018, he crashed at the Belgian Grand Prix (3) and in 2019, Hamilton won at the Bahrain Grand Prix while Leclerc saw his hopes of a first victor stripped (4). In 2020, he changed teams, joining Ferrari and pairing with Vettel (7). Leclerc and Hamilton are two of the sport's young champions, making the coming seasons particularly interesting (7). Virtual Grand Prix allowed fans to watch Leclerc race in a simulation of the cancelled event (6). In the 2020 2020 Formula One season, Leclerc fell just behind his rival, Sainz jr (8). Additionally, his godson, Godfather Charles Leclerc wore a tribute helmet to Bianchi and Leclerc's father at Monaco Grand Prix in 2020 (10). Th

Charles Leclerc qualifies for the 2nd race at the British Grand Prix.
Charles Leclerc races in the Virtual Grand Prix.
Charles Leclerc is confirmed as a Ferrari driver and will race alongside Sebastian Vettel.
Charles Leclerc finishes 2nd in the Tuscany Grand Prix, behind Lewis Hamilton.

Overview.Summary: The 2020 British Grand Prix could potentially be moved to August (8) due to the COVID-19 pandemic. Scuderia Ferrari ran a 2020 F1 car on the streets of Maranello (4). Sebastian Vettel and Ferrari announced their split at the end of the season (2). The race saw thrilling performances from drivers such as Max Verstappen (3) but was ultimately won by Mercedes (7). The 1,000th F1 race was also celebrated by Ferrari with special liveries (10). The event showcased classic cars, including a 1956/57 Mercedes-Benz W196 Grand Prix car that sold for $29.6 million at auction (9).

Timeline.Text: The Scuderia Ferrari team is featured in a multimedia album on the Ferrari website.
The British Grand Prix may be moved to August in order to save the race.
Charles Leclerc takes the 2020 F1 Ferrari on a test run through the streets of Maranello.
The Concours of Elegance in London showcases several classic Ferrari cars, including a 1956/57 Mercedes-Benz W196 Grand Prix car.
Sebastian Vettel and Scuderia Ferrari announce their split at the end of the 2020 season.
Ferrari marks their 1,000th F1 Grand Prix with special liveries for their car, driver suit, and helmet.

Overview.Summary: 2020 British Grand Prix was postponed along with other races (1,6,8,9). Red Bull Racing team was mentioned in relation to the Austrian Grand Prix being held at the Red Bull Ring (3,10). The race was originally scheduled for June 28th but was later rescheduled for July 5th (2). The 2020 season has been heavily impacted by the COVID-19 pandemic, causing a rescheduling and cancellation of multiple races (many included in the list of news articles provided) (4,5). Lewis Hamilton also criticized F1 for continuing with races during the pandemic (8).

Timeline.Text: Red Bull Racing announces the cancellation of Max Verstappen's contract due to conflicts with team management.
Red Bull Racing signs Sergio Perez as their new driver for the 2021 season.
Max Verstappen wins the Italian Grand Prix with a dominant performance, securing his fifth win of the season.
Red Bull Racing dominates the qualifying session of the Russian Grand Prix, with both Max Verstappen and Alex Albon securing the front row of the grid.
Max Verstappen narrowly misses out on a podium finish at the Nürburgring, finishing fourth at the Eifel Grand Prix.
Red Bull Racing announces that it has reached a settlement with Renault over the termination of their partnership.

Overview.Summary: Lewis Hamilton has had a successful year in 2020, despite the pandemic causing a number of changes to the Formula One (F1) season (2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 8, 10). He broke the track record at the British Grand Prix, earning pole position (1), and went on to win the Italian Grand Prix (3, 9). He has dominated the F1 championship (2). However, Hamilton has also been an active voice in social justice issues, such as the Black Lives Matter movement (10).

Timeline.Text: Lewis Hamilton secures pole position at the British Grand Prix in record time.
The 2020 Formula One calendar is confirmed, with Lewis Hamilton looking to defend his 2019 championship title.
Lewis Hamilton voices his opinion that the British Grand Prix and all of Formula One should not continue during the COVID-19 pandemic.
Lewis Hamilton wins the Monaco Grand Prix.
The 2020 Canadian Grand Prix is cancelled due to the pandemic, with Lewis Hamilton speaking out in support of the Black Lives Matter movement.
Lewis Hamilton competes in the Italian Grand Prix at the Autodromo Nazionale circuit.
Lewis Hamilton races in the Italian Grand Prix.
Lewis Hamilton is forced to compete on a virtual racing circuit due to the cancellation of the Australian Grand Prix.

Overview.Summary: In 2020, the Formula One World Championship faced significant impacts from the Covid-19 pandemic, with the season being postponed and races cancelled (2,4,6,9,10). The British government eventually cleared the path for the F1 season to resume, despite earlier concerns (6,8). The F1 season will see certain races, such as the British Grand Prix, held without fans in attendance (1,3, 5,7).

Timeline.Text: The Formula One season officially begins with the Austrian Grand Prix, the first of a double header in Austria.
The second race in Austria, a repeat of the previous race with no change in the results.
Formula One returns with no spectators at the British Grand Prix.
A repeat of the previous race, with no spectators present.

Overview.Summary: The 2020 British Grand Prix race has been confirmed with a revised calendar (5). The event is set to occur on August 2 and August 9 (1). The British Grand Prix has been secured for the next 17 years (4). There will also be a MotoGP event in 2020 (7). The Formula 1 schedule prior to the first part of the revised calendar occurring shows Austria as the starting location (5).

Timeline.Text: The 2020 Rolex British Grand Prix 2 begins, kicking off the revised 2020 F1 season.
The revised 2020 F1 season continues with the Portuguese Grand Prix.
McLaren creates a virtual track event to make up for the cancelled 2020 Australian Grand Prix.
British GP bosses secure a deal to keep the event at Silverstone for the next seventeen years.
The revised F1 calendar for the first half of the season is revealed, with the Austrian, Hungarian, and British Grand Prix confirmed.
The 2020 MotoGP British Grand Prix takes place at Silverstone.
The Heritage project at Silverstone reveals information about the 2021 British Grand Prix.
The 2020 Grand Prix de Monaco Historique is cancelled due to the COVID-19 pandemic.
F1's motorsport governing body confirms that F1's proposed return will follow guidelines from the UK government.

Overview.Summary: The 2020 British Grand Prix saw Lewis Hamilton win despite a tire failure on the final lap (1). The race result also featured Mercedes teammate Valtteri Bottas in second place (4) and Hamilton's potential 89th career win (6). The race also sparked discussions about the long-term future of the British Grand Prix (7).

Timeline.Text: Mercedes teammate Lewis Hamilton wins the 2020 British Grand Prix despite a tire failure on the final lap of the race.
Red Bull driver Max Verstappen crashes his car during the Styrian Grand Prix.
Mercedes completes the acquisition of the remaining 24.9% shareholding in Mercedes-Benz Grand Prix Limited previously held by management.
Lewis Hamilton and Valtteri Bottas take first and second place, respectively, at the 2020 British Grand Prix.
Valtteri Bottas sets the practice pace for the upcoming Russian Grand Prix.

Overview.Summary: The 2020 British Grand Prix (1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 7, 8, 9) confirmed its calendar for the first eight races of the season (7), with the race being held at Silverstone (1, 5, 7). This year, the Grand Prix will be affected by the global coronavirus pandemic, and as such, events leading up to the race have been canceled (6, 7, 8). It will take place at The Red Bull Ring in Austria (7) and The Autodromo Nazionale circuit in Monza (8). Historically, the race has been instrumental in fighting Nazism (10). Nigel Devereux references the Crystal Palace Grand Prix (10).

Timeline.Text: The British Grand Prix at Silverstone is officially confirmed as part of the 2020 Formula One season schedule.
The first eight races of the 2020 Formula One season are announced, including the British Grand Prix.
The first race of the 2020 Formula One season, the Austrian Grand Prix, begins at the Red Bull Ring.
The British Grand Prix is held at Silverstone Circuit, with Lewis Hamilton as the eventual winner.
The 2020 Formula One season continues with the British Grand Prix.
Mercedes' Lewis Hamilton competes in the Italian Grand Prix.
The 2020 Formula One season resumes with the Belgian Grand Prix.
European fans are able to attend the Italian Grand Prix in person.
The British Milers' Club Grand Prix takes place at Bedford's Trafford Gold Standard.
F1 driver Jorge Lorenzo achieves an impressive win at the store Championships.

Overview.Summary: The 2020 British Grand Prix took place on August 2, 2020 at the Silverstone Circuit in the United Kingdom. Lewis Hamilton of Mercedes F1 took pole position and went on to win the race (6, 7, 14). This was the 70th Anniversary Grand Prix at Silverstone (2, 6, 7). Other notable drivers included Charles Leclerc of Ferrari, who placed fourth, and Alexander Albon of Red Bull, who placed fifth (2). The race saw a new lap record by Hamilton (2, 6, 7). There were also several supporting events, including the Porsche Formula E Team's first win at the Berlin E-Prix and the premiere of the new Porsche 911 (10, 11, 14). The Autodromo Nazionale circuit in Monza, Italy hosted the Italian Formula One Grand Prix on September 6, 2020 (14). A similar event, the 42nd annual Long Beach Grand Prix, took place on April 29, 2016 in California, United States (20). Horse racing is a popular sport in the United Kingdom and other countries, with the Prix de l'Arc de Triomphe in Chantilly, France being a significant event (20). However, despite its popularity, there are concerns about the future of the British Grand Prix after 2009 (12). Races TV Schedule 2020 (Worldwide) provides a comprehensive list of supported channels and locations for viewing Formula One races (11).

Timeline.Text: Lewis Hamilton takes pole for the British Grand Prix in record time.
Lewis Hamilton wins the British Grand Prix despite a tire failure on the final lap.
Lewis Hamilton wins the Italian Grand Prix at Monza.
Pierre Gasly secures an unexpected victory at the 2020 F1 Italian Grand Prix at Monza.
Lewis Hamilton dominates at the Russian Grand Prix to tie Michael Schumacher's record of 91 F1 wins.
Ferrari prepares for the Grand Prix de France in Le Castellet.
Lewis Hamilton secures pole position at the Austrian Grand Prix.
George Russell's success in Formula 1 is no secret, but when will he receive the recognition he deserves?
Lewis Hamilton wins the 2020 F1 British Grand Prix and takes the lead in the championship.
Jorge Lorenzo bids an emotional farewell to MotoGP at the end of the season.
